A former Senator representing Bayelsa East Senatorial District, Ben Murray-Bruce, has lauded delegates at the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) National Convention for electing former Vice-President, Atiku Abubakar as its candidate for the 2023 presidential election. With 273 votes to  Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers state and 70 votes to former Senate President, Bukola Saraki, Atiku is set to be declared the winner of the primary. In a post on his official social media handle sighted by DAILY INDEPENDENT, Bruce said Atiku has the capacity to rebuild Nigeria. -Advertisement- He posted “I’m so excited! You can’t imagine. H.E Atiku has been my longtime friend and big brother, and I can vouch without any reservations for his character and capacity to rebuild this country, Nigeria”. “Our PDP delegates made the right choice. The process to rebuild Nigeria starts now”.